            <div class="card">
                <h5 class="card-header">*** 1. Engineer in specific category ***</h5>

                <div class="card-body">
                    <p class="card-text">(i) Civil engineering: Mainly used to build bridges, roads and tunnels, with the highest pass rate, mainly depending on the number of government infrastructure projects.</p>
                    <p class="card-text">(ii) Structure Engineering: It is mainly about the structure of the building and the field of mechanics, There is many calucaltion, and the pass rate is medium.</p>
                    <p class="card-text">(iii) Geotechnical Engineering: Mainly for excavation of retaining walls, etc., the pass rate is the lowest, so they are also the most valuable.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p></p>

            <div class="card">
                <h5 class="card-header">*** 2. Government trainee engineer ***</h5>

                <div class="card-body">
                    <p class="card-text">Special requirements:</p>
                    <p class="card-text">- Six months of special training in geology, site exploration and testing in the laboratory.</p>
                    <p class="card-text">- Twelve months of site experience.</p>
                    <p class="card-text">- Twelve months of office design experience.</p>
                    <p class="card-text">- Six months of in-depth technical and management responsibility training (may require internships with domestic government agencies)</p>
                </div>
            </div>
